<TITLE> 50 injured in Ashuganj tornado </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Pijush Kanti Acharya bdnews24.com Correspondent Brahmanbaria, July 25 (bdnews24.com)A quick tornado cut its path through five villages in Ashuganj upazila in Brahmanbaria, injuring at least 50 people and ruining over 100 homes Wednesday. The injured were given medical aid in the neighbourhood, witnesses said. The one-minute disaster struck the villages of Durgapur, Modhupur, Bahadurpur, Porapara and Baghmara at 9:45am. The tornado also downed electric poles supporting five kilometres of power cable through the upazila, disrupting power supply to hundreds of families. District relief and rehabilitation officer Abul Bakar and Ashuganj Upazila Nirbahi Officer AYM Ziauddin visited the ravaged villages. Bakar told bdnews24.com that a list of the affected families was being made. The local administration rushed 1,300kg of rice in immediate relief to the affected families. Seven people with serious injuries were given Tk 2,000 each for medical treatment. bdnews2
